  "notes": "Low German (Plattdeutsch / NedderdГјtsch). Descended from Old Saxon вЂ” NOT from Old High German. DID NOT UNDERGO the High German Consonant Shift: maken vs. German machen; water vs. German Wasser. Closely related to Dutch, Frisian, and Old English. Extremely diverse dialects across northern Germany and Netherlands. Now mostly spoken by elderly; listed as 'vulnerable' by UNESCO. Source: GallГ©e (1993), Robinson (1992). G ALLOPHONY: word-initial [ЙЎ], intervocalic [ЙЈ], coda/word-final [x] or [Г§] (front vowel context). Source: GallГ©e (1993).",
